  "prompt": "How do I change One Plus 3 ringtone?",
  "response": "Changing the ringtone on a OnePlus 3 is quite simple. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. **Open Settings**: Go to the settings app on your OnePlus 3.\n\n2. **Sound & Vibration**: Scroll down and select **\u201cSound & vibration\u201d**.\n\n3. **Ringtone**: Here, you will see an option for **\u201cPhone ringtone\u201d** or simply **\u201cRingtone\u201d**. Tap on it.\n\n4. **Select Ringtone**: A list of available ringtones will appear. You can listen to them by tapping on each option. \n\n5. **Add Custom Ringtones (Optional)**: If you want to use a custom ringtone, you can tap on the option to add from files. This requires you to have your desired ringtone file saved on your device. Navigate to the folder where your ringtone is stored.\n\n6. **Set Ringtone**: Once you find the ringtone you want, select it and then tap **\u201cOK\u201d** or **\u201cSave\u201d** to set it as your new ringtone.\n\n7. **Exit Settings**: Once you\u2019ve chosen your ringtone, you can exit out of the settings.\n\nYour new ringtone should now be set. You can test it by having someone call you or using the ringtone preview option.",
